    invalid reference

    instead.
    cn.nukkit.item.customitem.CustomItemDefinition.SimpleBuilder.addRepairs(List<String>, String)
    Legacy method for adding repair rules.

    This method writes minecraft:repairable.repair_items directly with a list of item names and a Molang expression for the repair amount. It only supports expression-based repair.

    Use CustomItemDefinition.SimpleBuilder.repairable(RepairEntry...) instead.

    • Support both numeric and expression-based repair amounts
    • Allow flexible argument styles (IDs, Items, Lists)
    cn.nukkit.item.customitem.CustomItemDefinition.SimpleBuilder.foil(boolean)
    Mojang have deprecated this component, prefer to use glint instead (foil and glint are the same).
    cn.nukkit.item.customitem.CustomItemDefinition.SimpleBuilder.makePersistent(boolean)
    to avoid misleading, use
    invalid reference 
    #shouldDespawn()
    instead. Make persistent component determines if the item should eventually despawn/or not while floating in the world
    cn.nukkit.item.customitem.CustomItemDefinition.SimpleBuilder.miningSpeed(float)
    Mining speed is not present in any Microsoft / Mojang docs, it might have deprecated as it also is part of item properties as most of legacy deprecated components. Prefer using CustomItemDefinition.SimpleBuilder.digger(cn.nukkit.item.utils.DiggerEntry...) component.
    cn.nukkit.item.customitem.CustomItemDefinition.SimpleBuilder.renderOffsets(RenderOffsets)
    This method was deprecated by Mojang and can suddenly stop working on Minecraft clients, prefer migrating your items to use resource_packs attachables. Control rendering offsets of custom items at different viewpoints
    cn.nukkit.item.customitem.CustomItemDefinition.toolBuilder(ItemCustomTool)
